text: Agata Tnasheva (born 6 February 1989) is an Kazakhstani female water polo player. She was a member of the Kazakhstan women's national water polo team. She was a part of the team at the 2009 World Aquatics Championships, and 2011 World Aquatics Championships. == References == Category:Kazakhstani water polo players Category:1989 births Category:Living people
